In the autumn morning, there was one giant grey on the lake shore;  
In its soft down, lightly waved by dripping droplets of dew and foggy mists;  
Beside it’s side stood an aged wood that held memories from far-away places—  
On this peaceful island, I sought solace as silent silence enveloped my senses…

White man eats delicately  
In Indian food and spice;
Black steel-meshed tabletop restraint—
